PERTH (miningweekly.com) – The Malaysian government has extended its Movement Control Order until May 12, meaning rare earths miner Lynas’ operations in the country would remain suspended. Operations at the Advanced Materials Plant was suspended in March as part of the country’s wider effort to halt the spread of the Covid-19 pandemic. The Movement Control Order had initially been extended from March 31 to April 14, but was now expected to be lifted on May 12.